AGI -&nbsp; US President Donald Trump opened the door to a possible trade agreement between the United States and the United Kingdom without duties, after a meeting with British Prime Minister, Keir Starmer. As part of a European offensive launched to ensure lasting peace in Ukraine, following the journey of French President Emmanuel Macron Monday, Starmer met the President of the United States at the White House yesterday on the eve of talks scheduled in Washington between Trump and Kiev leader, Volodymyr Zelensky. During the meeting and a subsequent press conference, Starmer and Trump exchanged unexpected friendliness: Trump described his colleague as a "special man" and a "great gentleman", while the Labour Premier praised the United States leader to "change speech" about Ukraine.
&nbsp;
