The Republican president has imposed duties on several countries in the first weeks of his first term, even using them to press allies to act, but he has allowed the United Kingdom to avoid this fate. Trump stated that the United Kingdom and the United States should conclude a "real trade agreement" without duties and called Sir Keir a "duro negotiator" who tried to convince him not to impose duties on the United Kingdom. "He's working hard, I'm telling you," said US President. "I think there are very good possibilities that we could conclude a real trade agreement where duties are not necessary. We'll see," said Trump.&nbsp;
